exchange, without materially diminishing the benefits to investors. Among other matters, the proposals would exempt
the class of debt securities from the restrictions on borrowing and the proxy rules. 

The costs to investors associated with these proposed rules and revisions are minimal. Currently, an issuer is not
required to register debt securities under the Exchange Act in order for those securities to be traded in the OTC market.
